HEADWORD: Umbilication
<hw>Um*bil"i*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A slight,
navel-like depression, or dimpling, of the center of a rounded body;
<as>as, the <ex>umbilication</ex> of a smallpox vesicle</as>; also, the
condition of being umbilicated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umbilicus</ent>⟦br⟧
